@node Assistance "If You Need Assistance" 
 
                          If You Need Assistance 
 
    We have made every effort to ensure that AccuPoint will be 
    reliable and that this manual is clear. However, nothing's 
    perfect. If you should have any problems with operating your 
    tablet, you can contact our Technical Support department at the 
    phone number and address below. We do ask however, that you check 
    the manual first. The answers to most questions can be found in 
    these pages, saving you the cost of a phone call. If you have 
    checked the manual and still have not resolved the problem please 
    write or call us at the following: 
 
                        TriMedia, Inc. 
                        AccuPoint Technical Support 
                        60 East Hintz Road 
                        Wheeling, IL 60090 
 
    Technical Support Phone Number: (708) 520-7502 
    There is no charge for technical support. 
 
    Please include or have available the following information: 
 
        · A detailed description of the problem. 
        · The version number of your AccuPoint software (see the 
        APConfig menu bar). 
        · Your software serial number. 
        · The version of Kickstart and Workbench you are using (1.3, 
        2.0 etc.). 
        · Your Amiga's configuration (model, memory, disk(s), etc.). 
        · The name and version of the program (if any) with which you 
        are having a problem (i.e. Deluxe Paint IV AGA). 
 
    We will try to resolve any problems you may have with AccuPoint 
    as expediently as possible. 
@endnode 
@node Warranty "Warranty" 
 
                                 Warranty 
 
    Your tablet and accessories (not software) are manufactured by 
    CalComp Inc., a world leader in computer graphics for over 30 
    years. The Tablet hardware is covered by a CalComp lifetime 
    limited warranty. The enclosed CalComp warranty certificate 
    explains the details of this warranty. 
 
    CalComp tablets are manufactured to the highest quality and 
    should provide you with years of service. In the event that you 
    should have a hardware problem PLEASE CONTACT TriMedia FIRST. The 
    customer service personnel at CalComp are not familiar with the 
    Amiga version of your tablet (only the IBM and Macintosh versions 
    which they sell directly). Calling us first will allow us to 
    better determine the nature of your problem and will allow us to 
    expedite any necessary warranty service at CalComp. DO NOT send a 
    suspect tablet to us or CalComp without contacting us first for a 
    return materials authorization number. You may call us at our 
    Technical Support Number (see the section titled 
    @{" If you need assistance " link Assistance} in this manual) if you are having a 
    hardware or software problem. 
 
    The "AccuPoint" software is sold "as-is". TriMedia, Inc. will, 
    for a period of ninety (90) days from date of purchase, replace 
    any defective media (diskettes) used in the manufacture of this 
    product. Replacement of defective media is the sole remedy 
    provided. TriMedia, Inc. makes no other warranties, express or 
    implied, including the implied warranties of fitness for a 
    particular purpose and merchantability. TriMedia will not be 
    liable for any special, consequential, indirect or incidental 
    damages, even if advised of their possibility. Some states do not 
    allow the exclusion or limitation of certain liabilities so the 
    above limitations may not apply to you. 
@endnode 
